# ALLOWLIST, not a blocklist. Everything is excluded by default; only the two paths the Dockerfile
# actually COPYs are let back in. A blocklist silently ships whatever you forget to add — and this
# repo contains plenty that must never reach the image or the daemon: developer skills (.claude/),
# CLAUDE.md, the AGENT-*.md Jira runbooks (which name internal hosts), scripts/, and .env.
#
# Consequence to remember: adding a new COPY to the Dockerfile means adding a matching `!` line here,
# or the build fails with "file not found". That failure is the point — it's louder than a leak.
*

# The pre-built jar (built on the host by setup.sh / docker.sh build — never inside Docker).
!scrum-mcp-server/build/libs/*.jar

# The capability skills and the Scrum Master agent, carried as a payload for
# `docker.sh install-skills`. NOT the developer skills in .claude/ — those are useless to a Scrum
# Master and shouldn't travel.
!.github/skills
!.github/agents
